label.value: normal protein localization to endosome

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the endosome(s) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: elongated vegetative cell with central constriction

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is elongated and has an abnormal shape featuring a constriction at the center of the cell, corresponding to the cell division site. In some such cells, the diameter at the ends is much greater than in wild-type cells.

definition.value: Note that cell with this phenotype, often called dumbbell-shaped, are usually also elongated. The distinction between this phenotype and swollen elongated cells (FYPO:0001429) is that dumbbell-shaped cells have a constriction along the long axis, whereas swollen elongated cells do not. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: increased punctate nuclear protein localization

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein is localized to discrete regions in the nucleus, visible as foci or dots by microscopy, to a greater extent observed than in normal (wild type) cells.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein that do not normally localize to discrete nuclear regions, or for proteins that do normally show punctate localization but with such localization increased in a mutant. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal transcription during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which transcription occurs to is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in extent, timing, start or termination site, etc. when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be measured.

label.value: decreased transcription during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which transcription occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

definition.value: Use this term if there is evidence, such as labeled nucleotide incorporation, showing that transcription rather than RNA stability is affected; otherwise, use 'decreased RNA level' (FYPO:0000826).

label.value: altered protein binding specificity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a mutation causes a gene product to bind to one or more proteins with different specificity from normal. For example, a protein may bind to a protein in a mutant that it does not bind in wild type. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: Also consider annotating to another term under 'abnormal protein binding', such as 'increased protein binding' (FYPO:0001571), to capture more details about the effect on protein binding specificity.

label.value: increased RNA level during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is greater than normal during the meiotic cell cycle. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased level of early meiotic gene mRNA during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA transcribed from early meiotic genes measured in a cell is lower than normal during the meiotic cell cycle. Early meiotic genes are normally transcribed during pre-meiotic S phase and recombination.

label.value: decreased level of middle meiotic gene mRNA during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA transcribed from middle meiotic genes measured in a cell is lower than normal during the meiotic cell cycle. Middle meiotic genes are normally transcribed during meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: decreased level of late meiotic gene mRNA during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA transcribed from late meiotic genes measured in a cell is lower than normal during the meiotic cell cycle. Late meiotic genes are normally transcribed during spore maturation.

label.value: increased level of early meiotic gene mRNA during late meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in late meiosis in which the amount of RNA transcribed from early meiotic genes measured in a cell is higher than normal. Early meiotic genes are normally transcribed during pre-meiotic S phase and recombination.

label.value: increased level of nitrogen starvation gene mRNA during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of one or more RNAs that are normally expressed during nitrogen starvation measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells) during the meiotic cell cycle.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: increased level of carbohydrate metabolism gene mRNA during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of one or more carbohydrate metabolism RNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells) during the meiotic cell cycle. Carbohydrate metabolism RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in carbohydrate metabolic processes.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: increased level of late meiotic gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA transcribed from late meiotic genes measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth). Late meiotic genes are normally transcribed during spore maturation.

label.value: increased level of middle meiotic gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA transcribed from middle meiotic genes measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth). Middle meiotic genes are normally transcribed during meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: increased level of heat shock gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more RNAs that are normally expressed during heat shock measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: spores sensitive to heat

value.value: A cell phenotype in which spores germinate to a lower extent than wild type following exposure to heat.

label.value: spores sensitive to ethanol

value.value: A cell phenotype in which spores germinate to a lower extent than wild type following exposure to ethanol.

label.value: spores sensitive to cell wall-degrading enzymes

value.value: A cell phenotype in which spores germinate to a lower extent than wild type following exposure to an enzymes that degrades cell wall polysaccharides.

label.value: decreased protein localization to ascospore wall

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the ascospore wall is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to micafungin

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to micafungin.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to linear element

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to linear elements is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal meiotic DNA double-strand break formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which generation of double-strand breaks at defined hotspots throughout the genome during meiosis I is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: delayed onset of meiotic DNA double-strand break formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which generation of double-strand breaks at defined hotspots throughout the genome during meiosis I begins later than normal.

label.value: normal meiotic recombination double-strand break repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the repair of double-strand breaks formed as part of meiotic recombination is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal meiotic recombination double-strand break repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the repair of double-strand breaks formed as part of meiotic recombination is abnormal.

label.value: abolished meiotic recombination double-strand break repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the repair of double-strand breaks formed as part of meiotic recombination does not occur.

label.value: decreased meiotic recombination double-strand break repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the repair of double-strand breaks formed as part of meiotic recombination is decreased.

label.value: decreased proteasome core complex binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of proteasome core complex binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abolished proteasome core complex binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which proteasome core complex binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased proteasome regulatory particle binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of proteasome regulatory particle binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abolished proteasome regulatory particle binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which proteasome regulatory particle binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: normal proteasome localization to nuclear periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a proteasome to the nuclear periphery is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished proteasome localization to nuclear periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a proteasome to the nuclear periphery is abolished.

label.value: increased protein localization to nuclear periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nuclear periphery is increased. The nuclear periphery is the portion of the nuclear lumen proximal to the inner nuclear membrane.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: septated spheroid vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is shaped in the form of a spheroid and has one or more septa.

label.value: resistance to enfumafungin

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of enfumafungin than normal.

label.value: resistance to pneumocandin B0

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of pneumocandin B0 than normal.

label.value: resistance to caspofungin

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of caspofungin than normal.

label.value: increased number of heterothallic h- cells

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a greater than normal number of cells in an originally homothallic (h90) population express M-specific information from the mat1 locus.

label.value: decreased protein localization to heterochromatin at mat2P silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to heterochromatin at the mat2P silent mating-type cassette is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased cellular ergosta-5,7,22,24(28)-tetraen-3beta-ol level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of ergosta-5,7,22,24(28)-tetraen-3beta-ol measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: abnormal ascus morphology

value.value: A phenotype characterized by altered ascus morphology, i.e. the size, shape, or structure of the ascus is abnormal.

label.value: normal ascus morphology

value.value: A phenotype characterized by normal ascus morphology, i.e. the size, shape, and structure of the ascus are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased cell wall (1->6)-beta-D-glucan level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of (1->6)-beta-D-glucan measured in the cell wall is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased DNA synthesis involved in mitotic DNA replication

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the synthesis of DNA that occurs as part of DNA replication is decreased.

label.value: normal cell cycle progression following cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cell cycle progression is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) after exposure to hydroxyurea.

label.value: delayed onset of cell cycle progression following cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cell cycle progression resumes after a longer time than normal after exposure to hydroxyurea.

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to salt stress is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to heat is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
